modules.description: Provides functions for encoding and decoding binary data using bit-level manipulation, including packing and unpacking sequences of bits into bytes. Works with byte arrays, bit streams, and integer values of varying widths. Used to serialize structured data for network transmission or file storage.

Provides functions to access and manipulate configuration settings using a higher-level interface based on ptime. Operates on a configuration data structure that encapsulates runtime parameters. Used to retrieve and manage time-related settings in environments requiring precise clock handling, such as web assembly targets.

Provides functions to handle HTTP response decompression and header updates. Operates on Cohttp_lwt.Response.t, Cohttp_lwt.Body.t, and Cohttp.Header.t types. Decompresses response bodies based on content-encoding headers, and ensures accept-encoding headers are set for compression support.

Provides functions to inflate and deflate strings using Deflate or Gzip algorithms, handling compressed data streams. Works with strings and configuration structures for compression settings. Enables decompression of HTTP response bodies and compression of data for output to files or streams.
